Had a lovely time visiting Brownsville Collaborative Middle School to see the opening of a community fridge.

The idea was inspired by a 7th grader who wanted to do more for people suffering from food inequality in her community. Bright future ahead for her.

Deed Theft is rampant throughout Brooklyn, so in 2021 we passed legislation to create a Cease and Desist Zone throughout Brooklyn.

But now, the Dept of State only wants to add one in East Flatbush.

We wrote a letter to them demanding they create a zone in ALL of Brooklyn, as the legislation intended.

If you would like to also tell the Dept of State to establish a Cease and Desist Zone in ALL of Brooklyn (and not just one part) you can email david.mossberg@dos.ny.gov

Public comments to their proposal will be accepted until January 23, 2023

We lost a community member this week. Adam Uster was cycling home with groceries when a truck turned into  the bike lane without looking on Lexington and Franklin in Clinton Hill.

This morning, community members gathered to hold a vigil, honor Adam, and fight for a protected bike lane. Let's get this done.

This is @uniquecstarks. She helps run @projectrestorebedstuy, an innovative justice model that takes gang-involved young men and places them in mentorship and dialogue with one another. They also receive wraparound services, targeted education, and trauma informed programming.

Tonight was their graduation ceremony. I'm so inspired by those young men. This is public safety. This is how we make our community stronger.
